    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "JavaScript HTML DOM - Changing CSS"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The HTML DOM allows JavaScript to change the style of HTML elements."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Changing HTML Style"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To change the style of an HTML element, use this syntax:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "unknown",
      "code": "document.getElementById(id).style.property = new style"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The following example changes the style of a <p> element:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "<html>\n<body>\n<p id=\"p2\">Hello World!</p>\n\n<script>\ndocument.getElementById(\"p2\").style.color = \"blue\";\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Using Events"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The HTML DOM allows you to execute code when an event occurs."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Events are generated by the browser when \"things happen\" to HTML elements:"
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "An element is clicked on\n  The page has loaded\n  Input fields are changed"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "You will learn more about events in the next chapter of this tutorial."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This example changes the style of the HTML element with id=\"id1\", when the \nuser clicks a button:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "<!DOCTYPE html><html><body><h1 id=\"id1\">My Heading 1</h1>\n<button type=\"button\" onclick=\"document.getElementById('id1').style.color = 'red'\">\nClick Me!</button></body></html>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "More Examples"
